=== Voice ===
Martin possesses a [[Tenor#Dramatic|dramatic tenor]] [[Voice type|vocal range]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=Rock N Roll Gold Rush: A Singles Un-Cyclopedia|last=Dean|first= Maury|year= 2003|publisher= Algora Publishing|isbn= 978-0-87586-227-9|page= 34|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i6RMBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA34|archive-date=January 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220117180530/https://books.google.com/books?id=i6RMBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA34|url-status=live}}</ref> Peter Gilstrap from ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' commented that his "powerful voice" is "capable of belt or lilt",<ref name="Variety performance">{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2007/music/markets-festivals/ricky-martin-4-1200559997/|title=Ricky Martin|work=Variety|last=Gilstrap|first=Peter|date=April 22, 2007|access-date=January 17, 2022|archive-date=January 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220117180615/https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/culture/ricky-martin-has-tel-aviv-livin-la-vida-loca-467788|url-status=live}}</ref> while ''[[The Jerusalem Post]]''{{'}}s Noa Amouyal described his voice as "soulful" and "very powerful".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/culture/ricky-martin-has-tel-aviv-livin-la-vida-loca-467788|title=Ricky Martin shakes his bon-bon (and everything else) in Tel Aviv|work=The Jerusalem Post|last=Amouyal|first=Noa|date=September 15, 2016|access-date=January 17, 2022|archive-date=January 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220117180615/https://www.jpost.com/israel-news/culture/ricky-martin-has-tel-aviv-livin-la-vida-loca-467788|url-status=live}}</ref> In 1995, Enrique Lopetegui of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' noted Martin's "improved vocal skills" on ''A Medio Vivir''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1995-12-05-ca-10662-story.html|title=Yes, There Really Is Life After Menudo : Pop music: After leaving the bubblegum band, Ricky Martin spent a year studying dance and vocals and moved to Mexico, where he starred in a musical and a soap opera. He's now a Latin pop star and a 'General Hospital' regular. That's not all.|work=Los Angeles Times|last=Lopetegui|first=Enrique|date=December 5, 1995|access-date=January 17, 2022|archive-date=January 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220117211639/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1995-12-05-ca-10662-story.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Also from the ''Los Angeles Times'', Ernesto Lechner later praised his vocal for being "charismatic enough to handle both ballads and up-tempo tunes".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1998/mar/01/entertainment/ca-24146|title=Record Rack|work=Los Angeles Times|first=Ernesto|last=Lechner|date=March 1998 |access-date=November 20, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605083113/http://articles.latimes.com/1998/mar/01/entertainment/ca-24146|archive-date=June 5, 2016}}</ref> Similarly, ''Billboard''{{'}}s [[Chuck Taylor (music journalist)|Chuck Taylor]] expressed "She's All I Ever Had" boasts "a versatility that contrasts nicely" with Martin's previous single, "Livin' la Vida Loca", labeling his vocal on the former "tender and heartfelt".<ref>{{cite magazine|year=1999|title=Reviews & Previews: Singles|magazine=Billboard|page=32|last=Taylor|first=Chuck|author-link=Chuck Taylor (music journalist)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kggEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA32|access-date=October 19, 2021|issn=0006-2510|volume=96|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019101614/https://books.google.com/books?id=kggEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA32|archive-date=October 19, 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Steve Gerrard of the ''Montreal Rocks'' complimented "his vocal maturity" on ''A Quien Quiera Escuchar''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://montrealrocks.ca/ricky-martin-announces-montreal-show/|title=Ricky Martin announces Montreal show|work=Montreal Rocks|last=Gerrard|first=Steve|date=March 31, 2015|access-date=January 17, 2022|archive-date=January 17, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220117211750/https://montrealrocks.ca/ricky-martin-announces-montreal-show/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Music videos and performances ===
''Billboard'' labeled Martin "a video icon", and ranked him as the 79th Greatest Music Video Artist of All Time in 2020, stating: "From the moment he sashayed up to the mic in 'Livin La Vida Loca' all dressed in black, and gave us that look, the Menudo alum became the most memorable and watchable drop-dead handsome guy in pop music."<ref name="BillboardGV">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/media/lists/100-best-music-video-artists-9440075/|title=The 100 Greatest Music Video Artists of All Time: Staff List|magazine=Billboard|access-date=May 24, 2021|date=August 27, 2020}}</ref> He has collaborated with various directors to produce his music videos, including Carlos Perez,<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.carlosperez.com/| title=Carlos Perez| publisher=Carlos Perez| access-date=January 18, 2022| archive-date=January 18, 2022| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118085546/https://www.carlosperez.com/| url-status=live}}</ref> [[Wayne Isham]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://los40.com/los40/2021/07/05/los40classic/1625494629_079015.html|title=Ricky Martin: La conexión de 'Livin' la vida loca' con Frank Sinatra, Madonna y James Bond|publisher=Los 40|last=Gomez|first=Alicia Sanchez|language=es|access-date=October 4, 2021|date=July 5, 2021|archive-date=October 4, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211004131925/https://los40.com/los40/2021/07/05/los40classic/1625494629_079015.html|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Jessy Terrero]],<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.univision.com/musica/wisin-decide-estrenar-tres-videos-musicales| title=Wisin decide estrenar tres videos musicales| publisher=[[Univision]]| access-date=June 26, 2021| date=November 2, 2015|language=Spanish| archive-date=November 7, 2015| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151107004902/https://www.univision.com/musica/wisin-decide-estrenar-tres-videos-musicales| url-status=live}}</ref> [[Simón Brand]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://peopleenespanol.com/article/ricky-martin-estreno-el-video-de-sencillo-la-mordidita-grabado-cartagena-de-indias-colombia-video/|title=Ricky Martin estrenó el video de 'La mordidita' (Video)|work=[[People en Español]]|last=Castro|first=Nohelia|language=es|date=June 12, 2015|access-date=January 18, 2022|archive-date=January 18, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118090129/https://peopleenespanol.com/article/ricky-martin-estreno-el-video-de-sencillo-la-mordidita-grabado-cartagena-de-indias-colombia-video/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Gustavo Garzón]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Ricky tomará vacaciones junto a Rebeca |url=https://www.elsiglodetorreon.com.mx/noticia/66026.ricky-tomara-vacaciones-junto-a-rebeca.html/ |website=El Siglo de Torreón |access-date=September 21, 2021 |language=es |date=December 21, 2003 |archive-date=September 21, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210921222145/https://www.elsiglodetorreon.com.mx/noticia/66026.ricky-tomara-vacaciones-junto-a-rebeca.html/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Nigel Dick]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nigeldick.com/films/productions-1999/|title=Productions 1999|publisher=[[Nigel Dick]]|access-date=October 23, 2021|archive-date=October 23, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023131916/https://www.nigeldick.com/films/productions-1999/|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Kacho López Mari|Kacho Lopez]],<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-tiburones-video-8548902/|title=Ricky Martin Proclaims Peace With Powerful Ballad 'Tiburones': Watch the Video|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|magazine=Billboard|access-date=January 24, 2020|date=January 23, 2020}}</ref> and Memo del Bosque.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rzg.pl/audycja/ricky-martin-maria/|title=Ricky Martin - Maria|last=Jankowska|first=Katarzyna|publisher=Radio Zielona Góra|access-date=August 27, 2021|date=September 10, 2018|language=Polish|archive-date=August 27, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210827193133/https://www.rzg.pl/audycja/ricky-martin-maria/|url-status=live}}</ref> "Livin' la Vida Loca" was nominated for [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] at the [[1999 MTV Video Music Awards]], making Martin the first Latin artist in history to receive a nomination in this category.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2021-09-09-5-best-hip-hop-moments-from-the-1999-mtv-video-music-awards/|title=5 Best Hip Hop Moments From The 1999 MTV Video Music Awards|last=Anthony|first=Kiyonna|publisher=[[iHeartRadio]]|access-date=September 11, 2021|date=September 10, 2021}}</ref> It won a total of five awards at the ceremony,<ref name="BillboardGV"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/38702/livin-la-vida-flashback|title=Livin' La Vida Flashback|last=Marti|first=Diana|publisher=[[E!]]|date=September 14, 1999|access-date=May 24, 2021}}</ref> making it rank among [[MTV Video Music Awards#Most wins for a single video|the videos with most wins in the history of the MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goldderby.com/gallery/mtv-video-music-awards-most-wins-of-all-time/vma-most-wins-ricky-martin-livin-la-vida-loca/|title=MTV Video Music Awards: Most Wins Of All Time|publisher=[[Gold Derby]]|date=August 6, 2018|access-date=May 24, 2021}}</ref> The explicit sexual scenes of the music video for "She Bangs" were met with criticism from the audience; several [[Television in the United States|American television]] stations cut the scenes when airing the video. According to the ''[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]'''s John Dingwall, with the visual, Martin ditched his teen idol image by transforming to a more mature one.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-65721794.html|title=Off the Record: Risque Martin, Latin Star's New Video is Sizler|work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]|last=Dingwall|first=John|date=October 4, 2000|access-date=December 15, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413163642/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-65721794.html|archive-date=April 13, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was consequently banned in several Latin American countries, such as the Dominican Republic.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://h.elsiglodetorreon.com.mx/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib:LowLevelEntityToSaveGifMSIE_ELSIGLO&Type=text/html&Locale=spanish-skin-custom&Path=EDT/2000/11/20&ChunkNum=-1&ID=Ar04517&PageLabel=45|title=¿Chismosa yo? ...¡para nada!|language=es|newspaper=El Siglo de Torreón|page=45|date=November 20, 2000|access-date=January 11, 2015}}</ref> Martin told [[MTV News]] that the video represented freedom rather than his sexuality.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ricky Martin, un canto a la ambigüedad sexual|url=http://archivo.lavoz.com.ar/2000/1206/nota3635_1.htm|access-date=December 15, 2014|work=[[La Voz del Interior]]|date=December 6, 2000|language=es}}</ref> The video was awarded Best Music Video at the 2nd Annual Latin Grammy Awards, Best Clip of the Year — Latin at the 2001 ''Billboard'' Music Video Awards, and [[Lo Nuestro Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]] at the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 2001|13th Lo Nuestro Awards]].<ref name="billboard.com"/><ref name="Billboard MV Award">{{cite magazine|year=2001|title=Gorillaz, Fatboy Slim Top Video Awards|magazine=Billboard|page=10|last=Hay|first=Carla|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ExIEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA10|access-date=February 9, 2022|issn=0006-2510|volume=104}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://i.univision.com/contentuvn/rinconlatino/plnuestro/images/index_historia.swf|title=Lo Nuestro – Historia|language=es|publisher=Univision|access-date=March 8, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626102925/http://i.univision.com/contentuvn/rinconlatino/plnuestro/images/index_historia.swf|archive-date=June 26, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Martin has been noticed for "dance moves of his own" and his "[[Shake Your Bon-Bon|bon-bon shaking]] dance moves".<ref name="Billboard Acting"/><ref name="Billboard Vida Performance">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/ricky-martin-vida-2014-billboard-music-awards-6084953/|title=Ricky Martin Performs 'Vida' at 2014 Billboard Music Awards|magazine=Billboard|last=Payne|first=Chris|date=May 18, 2014|access-date=January 18, 2022}}</ref> Carol Sandoval from [[Batanga Media|VIX]] named him the "best dancer on any stage worldwide", highlighting his hips movement and "successful turns".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vix.com/es/cultura-pop/210551/estos-7-famosos-prueban-que-los-latinos-son-los-dioses-del-baile-sabroso|title=7 famosos prueban que los latinos son los que bailan más sabroso|publisher=[[Batanga Media|VIX]]|last=Sandoval|first=Carol|language=es|access-date=January 18, 2022|archive-date=January 19, 2022}}</ref> He was ranked as the ninth best male dancer by the ''[[Evening Standard]]'' and the tenth Male Singer Who Can Dance by [[WatchMojo]], being the only Latin entertainer on both lists.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/the-best-dancers-men-6977111.html|title=The best dancers: men|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=April 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://watchmojo.com/video/id/15981|title=Top 10 Male Singers Who Can Dance|publisher=[[WatchMojo]]|access-date=January 18, 2022|archive-date=January 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119023149/https://watchmojo.com/video/id/15981|url-status=live}}</ref> Writing for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', Scott Feinberg introduced Martin as "an incredible dancer".<ref name="HRCup"/> ''Billboard''{{'}}s Jessica Roiz labeled him "a true showman", noting his "many outfit changes", "various dance performances", and "different stage set for each song".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-enrique-iglesias-tour-miami-concert-highlights-9650112/|title=Enrique Iglesias & Ricky Martin Bring Latin Pop Nostalgia to Miami Concert: Highlights|magazine=Billboard|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|date=October 23, 2021|access-date=January 18, 2022}}</ref> [[Jon Pareles]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'' described him as "an all-around showman" and ''Variety''{{'}}s Peter Gilstrap called him "every inch the showman", both recognizing his vocal abilities, while the former also commented he is "a dancer as muscular and hard-working as anyone in his troupe", mentioning his "likable, good-hearted character" and "steadfast Puerto Rican pride".<ref name="Variety performance"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/16/arts/music/16mart.html|title=Planting a Love Seed at the Garden|work=The New York Times|last=Pareles|first=Jon|date=October 16, 2007|access-date=January 18, 2022}}</ref> Music critics have mostly praised his concerts for the choreographies, video screens, visual effects, stage, Latin influences, and Martin's vocals, costume changes, energy, sensuality, dance moves, and gestures, while the quality of sounds and sound mixes have received mixed reviews.<ref>Reviews on Martin's tours and concerts:
