ion".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/aug/09/brazilian-pop-superstar-anitta-interview|title=Brazilian pop sensation Anitta: 'Run for president? I'm 27!'|last=Lopez|first=Julyssa|work=The Guardian|date=August 9, 2020|access-date=February 3, 2022}}</ref>

===Portrayal in television===
{{Main|Súbete a Mi Moto (2020 TV series)|l1=Súbete a Mi Moto}}
In July 2019, SOMOS Productions, [[Endemol Shine Group|Endemol Shine Boomdog]], and Piñolywood Studios announced the production of a [[Biographical film|biographical]] [[web television]] series about [[Menudo (group)|Menudo]], titled ''[[Súbete a Mi Moto (2020 TV series)|Subete a Mi Moto]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/menudo-series-subete-a-mi-moto-8523561/|title=A Menudo Series Is In the Works: Here's What to Know About 'Súbete a Mi Moto'|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|magazine=Billboard|date=July 23, 2019|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080005/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/menudo-series-subete-a-mi-moto-8523561/|url-status=live}}</ref> Consisting of 15 episodes of 60 minutes each, the series premiered on [[Amazon Prime Video]] on October 9, 2020, in Mexico, Latin America, and Spain. It was filmed in Mexico and Puerto Rico, and Martin was portrayed by actors Felipe Albors and Ethan Schwartz. The series premiered in the United States on February 14, 2021, on [[Estrella TV]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/subete-a-mi-moto-basada-en-la-historia-del-grupo-menudo-premiering-october-9-exclusively-in-amazon-prime-video-brings-back-the-most-successful-latin-boy-band-301147054.html|title='Súbete A Mi Moto', Basada En La Historia Del Grupo Menudo, Premiering October 9 Exclusively In Amazon Prime Video, Brings Back The Most Successful Latin Boy Band|publisher=[[PR Newswire]]|date=October 6, 2020|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080015/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/subete-a-mi-moto-basada-en-la-historia-del-grupo-menudo-premiering-october-9-exclusively-in-amazon-prime-video-brings-back-the-most-successful-latin-boy-band-301147054.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/subete-a-mi-moto-estrella-tv-date-9519192/|title=Menudo-Inspired Series 'Súbete A Mi Moto' to Premiere on Estrella TV|last=Flores|first=Griselda|magazine=Billboard|date=February 1, 2021|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080022/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/subete-a-mi-moto-estrella-tv-date-9519192/|url-status=live}}</ref> On the review aggregation website Tomatazos, the first season has a positive score of 75%. The website's critical consensus summary states, "A good trip to the past that recalls a band that defined the youth of a certain public, but that doesn't ignore the darkest moments in the lives of its members."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tomatazos.com/series/512718/Subete-a-mi-moto/temporada/1|title=Menudo-Inspired Series 'Súbete A Mi Moto' to Premiere on Estrella TV|publisher=Tomatazos|language=es|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080034/https://www.tomatazos.com/series/512718/Subete-a-mi-moto/temporada/1|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Other ventures==
===Books===
On August 19, 2010, Martin announced that he had been working on his [[memoir]], mentioning its title as ''Me'' and publish date as November 2, 2010. He expressed that writing the book was "one of the reasons" he decided to come out earlier that year. The book also had a Spanish edition title ''Yo'' ({{trans|''I''}}), which was published simultaneously by Celebra. He stated that writing his memoir allowed him "to explore the different paths and experiences" that have led him to be who he is, noting that it "was not easy but allowed for an incredible spiritual journey".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2010/08/ricky-martins-memoir-due-november-2/|title=Ricky Martin's memoir due November 2|work=[[LGBTQ Nation]]|date=August 19, 2010|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080159/https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2010/08/ricky-martins-memoir-due-november-2/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elmundo.es/america/2010/08/19/gentes/1282233222.html|title=Ricky Martin contará todo sobre su homosexualidad en una biografía|work=El Mundo|language=es|date=August 20, 2010|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080220/https://www.elmundo.es/america/2010/08/19/gentes/1282233222.html|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Me'' spent several weeks at number one on [[the New York Times Best Seller list]].<ref name="MW Nightclub">{{Cite web|url=https://www.metroweekly.com/2016/08/ricky-martin/|title=Exclusive: Ricky Martin on the power of music, Pulse Nightclub, and why he supports Hillary|last=Shulman|first=Randy|work=[[Metro Weekly]]|date=August 18, 2016|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080230/https://www.metroweekly.com/2016/08/ricky-martin/|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2019, ''¡Hola!'' staff ranked the book among "12 Books by Celebrities to Inspire and Motivate You", while ''Book Riot'' placed it on an unranked list of the "Best Celebrity Books You Should Read This Year" in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/2019042523253/celebrity-books-to-inspire/|title=12 Books by Celebrities to Inspire and Motivate You|work=¡Hola!|date=April 25, 2019|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080249/https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/2019042523253/celebrity-books-to-inspire/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bookriot.com/best-celebrity-books/|title=40+ Celebrity Books You Should Read This Year|last=Pereira|first=Carina|work=Book Riot|date=January 28, 2020|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080347/https://bookriot.com/best-celebrity-books/|url-status=live}}</ref> Martin's first children's book ''Santiago the Dreamer in Land Among the Stars'' was published by Celebra and illustrated by Patricia Castelao in November 2013 for ages between five and nine. Its Spanish-language edition, ''Santiago El Soñador en Entre Las Estrellas'', was published simultaneously. Martin expressed that the book was inspired by his "personal life, with fantasy added to it", as well as "a lot of [[cartoon]]s".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/books/2013/11/11/ricky-martin-childrens-book/3500029/|title=Find Ricky Martin's first kids' book 'Among the Stars'|last=Deutsch|first=Lindsay|work=USA Today|date=November 11, 2013|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080315/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/books/2013/11/11/ricky-martin-childrens-book/3500029/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diariodepontevedra.es/articulo/noticias/patricia-castelao-la-dibujante-pontevedresa-del-nino-de-ricky-martin/20140115180800245779.html|title=Patricia Castelao, la dibujante pontevedresa del niño de Ricky Martin|last=Álvarez|first=Miguel|work=[[Diario de Pontevedra]]|language=es|date=January 15, 2014|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080325/https://www.diariodepontevedra.es/articulo/noticias/patricia-castelao-la-dibujante-pontevedresa-del-nino-de-ricky-martin/20140115180800245779.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Products and endorsements===
Martin endorsed the 2012 Viva Glam campaign with Trinidadian rapper [[Nicki Minaj]], which raised $270 million for the [[Mac AIDS Fund]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Rodriguez|first=Cindy Y.|title=Nicki Minaj And Ricky Martin Promote MAC Viva Glam, Bring HIV/AIDS Awareness To Latin America|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/nicki-minaj-and-ricky-martin-promote-mac-new-campaign-hiv-aids-awareness-latin-america_n_1282031|work=HuffPost|access-date=May 27, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=White|first=Belinda|title=Mac Viva Glam sales raise $250 million for AIDS Fund|date=July 26, 2012|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/beauty/news-features/TMG9429598/MAC-VIVA-GLAM-sales-raise-250-million-for-AIDS-Fund.html|work=The Daily Telegraph|access-date=June 9, 2020}}</ref> In October 2020, Martin announced that he would launch his company, Martin Music Lab in partnership with music engineers [[Jaycen Joshua]] and Michael Seaberg. The company is centered around a new audio technique called "Orbital Audio", that "creates a new type of immersive, headphone listening experience". Martin used the technique on his EP ''Pausa'', while several artists including Bad Bunny, [[Residente]], [[Myke Towers]], and [[ASAP Rocky|A$AP Rocky]] are going to work with the company. The latter plans to release his whole upcoming studio album, using "Orbital Audio". Martin is going to expand the technique "beyond the music industry and tap into the movies, sports and, most notably, the wellness and meditation space".<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/ricky-martin-music-lab-orbital-audio-launch-immersive-listening/|title=Ricky Martin Launches Martin Music Lab, With Focus On 'Elevating' Audio Entertainment Experiences|magazine=Billboard|date=October 8, 2020|access-date=February 4, 2022|archive-date=February 4, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220204162409/https://www.billboard.com/pro/ricky-martin-music-lab-orbital-audio-launch-immersive-listening/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cathyolson/2020/10/08/ricky-martin-launches-company-to-expand-his-orbital-audio-immersive-techeyes-gaming-mental-health-apps/?sh=5a8556107ce7|title=Ricky Martin Launches Company To Expand His Orbital Audio Immersive Tech - Eyes Gaming, Mental Health Apps|last=Olson|first=Cathy Applefeld|work=Forbes|date=October 8, 2020|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080415/https://www.forbes.com/sites/cathyolson/2020/10/08/ricky-martin-launches-company-to-expand-his-orbital-audio-immersive-techeyes-gaming-mental-health-apps/?sh=5a8556107ce7|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2021, Martin partnered with [[skin care]] company Kumiko. The skincare line, created by Chilean [[Cosmetology|cosmetologist]] Catalina Aguirre, is the first to combine "[[mesotherapy]], [[matcha]], and cutting-edge European technology into unique multi-action formulas that penetrate the dermis with powerful anti-aging properties and lifting benefits".<ref name="Buena Vida God"/><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/holiday-latin-gift-guide-2021-1235002502/|title=Ultimate 2021 Holiday Latin Gift Guide: Natti Natasha's Wine, The Bad Bunny Shoes, Pitbull's CBD Goodies & More|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|magazine=Billboard|date=November 24, 2021|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=February 5, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220205080428/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/holiday-latin-gift-guide-2021-1235002502/|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Activism ==
=== Philanthropy ===
[[File:Ricky Martin Foundation.jpg|180px|The Ricky Martin Foundation logo|thumb|left]]
While on a trip to India in 2002, Martin witnessed three [[Minor (law)|minor]] girls who were about to be sold into prostitution and rescued them. The following year, he became a UNICEF [[Goodwill ambassador|Goodwill Ambassador]] and then met with activists and decided to fight against [[human trafficking]], which is the second-most lucrative crime in the world. In 2004, Martin launched the Ricky Martin Foundation, a non-profit, non-governmental organization that focuses on denouncing human trafficking and educating about the crime's "existence through research and community initiatives, anchored in the defense of children and youth rights".<ref name="RM Foundation">{{Cite web|url=http://rickymartinfoundation.org/about/|title=About Us|publisher=The Ricky Martin Foundation|access-date=February 5, 2022|archive-date=July 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706194942/http://rickymartinfoundation.org/about/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rickymartinfoundation.org/about-us/|title=¿Quiénes somos?|publisher=The Ricky Martin Foundation|language=es|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073023/https://rickymartinfoundation.org/about-us/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/united-nations-day-25-celebrity-833717/13-ricky-martin/|title=United Nations Day: 25 Celebrity U.N. Ambassadors (Photos)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 24, 2015 |access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073033/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/united-nations-day-25-celebrity-833717/13-ricky-martin/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same year, he [[appeal]]ed to the [[United Nations]] for international help to fight against [[sex tourism]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unicef.org/goodwill-ambassadors/ricky-martin|title=Ricky Martin|publisher=[[UNICEF]]|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073033/https://www.unicef.org/goodwill-ambassadors/ricky-martin|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2005, following the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami]], Martin visited Thailand to assess the needs of the minor survivors who were "extremely vulnerable to traffickers". Later that year, the Ricky Martin Foundation signed an alliance in partnership with [[Habitat for Humanity]] to construct 224 homes for the tsunami-affected families. The project was completed in December 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://reliefweb.int/report/thailand/thailand-ricky-martin-foundation-and-habitat-humanity-announce-completion|title=Thailand: Ricky Martin Foundation and Habitat for Humanity announce completion of partnership to help tsunami-affected families|publisher=[[ReliefWeb]]|date=December 21, 2006|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073054/https://reliefweb.int/report/thailand/thailand-ricky-martin-foundation-and-habitat-humanity-announce-completion|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2006, the foundation collaborated with the [[International Organization for Migration]] in the Llama y Vive ({{trans|Call and Live}}) campaign, which focuses on facilitating "the prevention of human trafficking and the protection of young people, victims of child trafficking and prosecution of traffickers".<ref name="RM Foundation"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theyucatantimes.com/2019/09/ricky-martin-received-the-peace-summit-award/|title=Ricky Martin received the Peace Summit Award|work=The Yucatan Times|date=September 23, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073106/https://www.theyucatantimes.com/2019/09/ricky-martin-received-the-peace-summit-award/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In January 2010, along with many celebrities, Martin operated the [[charitable organization|charity]] [[telethon]] ''[[Hope for Haiti Now]]'' to raise donations for the [[2010 Haiti earthquake]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/hope-for-haiti-now-a-global-benefit-for-earthquake-relief-announces-superstar-lineup-of-operators-standing-by-82393422.html|title='Hope for Haiti Now: A Global Benefit for Earthquake Relief' Announces Superstar Lineup of Operators Standing By|publisher=PR Newswire|date=January 22, 2010|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073118/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/hope-for-haiti-now-a-global-benefit-for-earthquake-relief-announces-superstar-lineup-of-operators-standing-by-82393422.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, the Ricky Martin Foundation created the first program of community [[Social actions|social action]] against child trafficking in Martin's native Puerto Rico, titled "Se Trata" ({{trans|"It is About"}}). In 2012, the foundation participated in the making of the Child Protection Model Law on the [[International Centre for Missing & Exploited Children]].<ref name="RM Foundation"/> In 2016, Martin visited [[Syrians in Lebanon#Syrian refugees in Lebanon|Syrian refugees in Lebanon]] and played with the children and talked to them in an informal [[refugee camp]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/ricky-martin-visits-syrian-refugees-in-lebanon|title=Ricky Martin visits Syrian refugees in Lebanon|date=December 2, 2016|publisher=Fox News|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073124/https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/ricky-martin-visits-syrian-refugees-in-lebanon|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the [[Hurricane Maria]] in Puerto Rico in 2017, the Ricky Martin Foundation helped people and handed over homes that were rebuilt after the losses; Martin launched a viral campaign of selling a black [[T-shirt]] with the Puerto Rican flag stamped on it in order to raise the funds. The T-shirts were designed by Martin's twin boys Matteo and Valentino, while many celebrities including [[Will Smith]], Bad Bunny, Marc Anthony, Luis Fonsi, and Maluma supported the campaign.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-keys-reconstructed-houses-puerto-rico-8487747/amp/|title=Ricky Martin Delivers Keys of Reconstructed Houses to Families Left Homeless by Puerto Rican Hurricanes|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|magazine=Billboard|date=December 3, 2018|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073152/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-keys-reconstructed-houses-puerto-rico-8487747/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref> During the COVID-19 pandemic, Martin created a campaign to help health care workers through the non-profit organization Project Hope. He expressed: "As you know, health care professionals are extremely vulnerable and professionals around the world don’t have personal protection equipment they need to prevent them getting infected."<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-health-care-workers-coronavirus-project-hope-9340908/amp/|title=Ricky Martin Launches Campaign to Keep Health Workers Safe Amid Coronavirus|last=Fernandez|first=Suzette|magazine=Billboard|date=March 23, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073143/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-health-care-workers-coronavirus-project-hope-9340908/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2021, Martin collaborated with [[Antonia Novello]] to launch mass vaccination events in Puerto Rico.<ref>{{cite news| last=Rosa | first=Bárbara J. Figueroa | title=Ricky Martin: 'Así se logran los sueños: cuando nos unimos por un mismo propósito'| newspaper=[[Primera Hora (Puerto Rico)|Primera Hora]]| date=February 10, 2021 | url=https://www.primerahora.com/noticias/gobierno-politica/notas/ricky-martin-asi-se-logran-los-suenos-cuando-nos-unimos-por-un-mismo-proposito/ | language=es | access-date=April 2, 2021|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073228/https://www.primerahora.com/noticias/gobierno-politica/notas/ricky-martin-asi-se-logran-los-suenos-cuando-nos-unimos-por-un-mismo-proposito/|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the [[murder of George Floyd]] and [[Black Lives Matter]] protests in 2020, Martin honored an effort called "Black Out Tuesday" and launched the hashtag #knowthestruggle, giving his social media to the voices of the community that are "looking for justice", to learn more about what is happening.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/black-out-tuesday-musicians-participating-9395160/amp/|title=Rihanna, Ricky Martin, Green Day, Katy Perry, Normani & Many Others Honor Black Out Tuesday|magazine=Billboard|date=June 2, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073313/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/black-out-tuesday-musicians-participating-9395160/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oprahdaily.com/entertainment/a32908634/ricky-martin-quarantine-pausa-interview/|title=Ricky Martin Reveals How His New EP, Pausa Helped Him Overcome Quarantine Anxiety|last=Davis|first=Arianna|work=O, The Oprah Magazine|date=June 18, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073240/https://www.oprahdaily.com/entertainment/a32908634/ricky-martin-quarantine-pausa-interview/|url-status=live}}</ref>

For his humanitarian efforts and fighting against human trafficking, Martin has been honored with numerous accolades, including the Peace Summit Award by the [[World Summit of Nobel Peace Laureates]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com.mx/ricky-martin-recibe-premio-por-la-paz-y-se-pronuncia-por-derechos-lgbt-en-yucatan/|title=Ricky Martin recibe premio por la paz y se pronuncia por derechos LGBT en Yucatán|last=Navarro|first=María Fernanda|work=Forbes|language=es|date=September 21, 2019|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130912/https://www.forbes.com.mx/ricky-martin-recibe-premio-por-la-paz-y-se-pronuncia-por-derechos-lgbt-en-yucatan/|url-status=live}}</ref> the TIP Report Hero Award by the [[United States Department of State]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tipheroes.org/ricky-martin/|title=Ricky Martin|publisher=[[United States Department of State|United States Department of State Trafficking in Persons Report]]|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130950/http://www.tipheroes.org/ricky-martin/|url-status=live}}</ref> the [[Billboard Spirit of Hope Award|Spirit of Hope Award]] by [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Juan Gabriel Cleans Up At Billboard Latin Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/juan-gabriel-cleans-up-at-billboard-latin-awards-75804/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=February 6, 2022|date=May 10, 2002|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130951/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/juan-gabriel-cleans-up-at-billboard-latin-awards-75804/|url-status=live}}</ref> the [[Latin Recording Academy Person of the Year]] Award,<ref name="Grammy"/> the Award of Inspiration by amfAR Gala,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/entertainment-news/2010/06/04/ricky-martin-honored-amfar-gala|title=Ricky Martin Honored at amfAR Gala|last=Bolcer|first=Julie|work=Advocate|date=June 4, 2010|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130932/https://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/entertainment-news/2010/06/04/ricky-martin-honored-amfar-gala|url-status=live}}</ref> the Leader of Change Award by the Foundation for Social Change,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tipheroes.org/resources/ricky-martin/ricky-martin-unicef-goodwill-ambassador-accepts-the-leader-of-change-award/|title=Ricky Martin, UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador, Accepts the Leader of Change Award|publisher=United States Department of State Trafficking in Persons Report|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130946/http://www.tipheroes.org/resources/ricky-martin/ricky-martin-unicef-goodwill-ambassador-accepts-the-leader-of-change-award/|url-status=live}}</ref> the Humanitarian Award by the Global Gift Foundation,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalgiftfoundation.org/awards/|title=Awards|date=November 11, 2019 |publisher=Global Gift Foundation|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206130950/https://www.globalgiftfoundation.org/awards/|url-status=live}}</ref> the Humanitarian Award by the [[Hispanic Federation]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hispanicfederation.org/media/press_releases/hispanic_federations_star-studded_gala_raises_23_million_dollars/|title=Hispanic Federation's Star-Studded Gala Raises $2.3 Million Dollars|publisher=[[Hispanic Federation]]|date=April 19, 2018|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206131024/https://www.hispanicfederation.org/media/press_releases/hispanic_federations_star-studded_gala_raises_23_million_dollars/|url-status=live}}</ref> the Corazón Latino Award by the [[iHeartRadio Fiesta Latina]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telemundo.com/entretenimiento/iheartradio-fiesta-latina/ricky-martin-es-honrado-con-el-premio-corazon-latino-de-iheartradio-fotos-tmna1707070|title=Ricky Martin es honrado con el Premio Corazón Latino de iHeartRadio (Fotos)|publisher=Telemundo|language=es|date=November 3, 2017|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206131038/https://www.telemundo.com/entretenimiento/iheartradio-fiesta-latina/ricky-martin-es-honrado-con-el-premio-corazon-latino-de-iheartradio-fotos-tmna1707070|url-status=live}}</ref> the International Humanitarian Award by the International Center for Missing and Exploited Children,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2011/10/lgbt-history-month-profile-grammy-award-winning-artist-ricky-martin/?amp|title=LGBT History Month profile: Grammy award-winning artist Ricky Martin|work=LGBTQ Nation|date=October 22, 2011|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206131052/https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2011/10/lgbt-history-month-profile-grammy-award-winning-artist-ricky-martin/?amp|url-status=live}}</ref> the Agent of Change Award by the International Peace Honors,<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/uplifting-moments-latin-music-thalia-pitbull-9455801/amp/|title=5 Uplifting Moments in Latin Music This Week (September 26)|last=Roiz|first=Jessica|magazine=Billboard|date=September 26, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206131029/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/uplifting-moments-latin-music-thalia-pitbull-9455801/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref> the PODER Social Leadership Awards,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://poderawards.com/2012-awardees/|title=2013 Awardees|publisher=PODER Business Awards|date=November 6, 2013|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131205203905/http://poderawards.com/2012-awardees/|url-status=dead}}</ref> and the Agent of Change Award by the [[Premios Juventud]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elnuevodia.com/entretenimiento/musica/notas/premios-juventud-reconoce-a-ricky-martin-por-ser-un-agente-de-cambio-en-el-mundo/|title=Premios Juventud reconoce a Ricky Martin por ser un agente de cambio en el mundo|last=Mercado|first=Damaris Hernández|work=El Nuevo Día|language=es|date=August 14, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206131054/https://www.elnuevodia.com/entretenimiento/musica/notas/premios-juventud-reconoce-a-ricky-martin-por-ser-un-agente-de-cambio-en-el-mundo/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Politics ===
[[File:Ricky Martin in Congress.jpg|thumb|right|Martin (mid-right) in Congress, with [[Luis Fortuño]] (far left), [[Tom Lantos]] (mid-left) and [[Chris Smith (New Jersey politician)|Chris Smith]] (far right).]]
On January 20, 2001, during the [[first inauguration of George W. Bush|first inauguration]] of [[George W. Bush]], Martin performed "The Cup of Life" and danced with him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/inauguration-performances-werent-always-so-contentious-highlights-from-the-last-75-years/2017/01/11/33de4cc2-d5e9-11e6-9a36-1d296534b31e_story.html|title=Inauguration performances weren't always so contentious: Highlights from the last 75 years|last=Merry|first=Stephanie|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=January 12, 2019|access-date=May 7, 2021|archive-date=May 7, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210507110752/https://www.aftonbladet.se/noje/9905/17/meja.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/presidential-inauguration-pop-music-performance-timeline-trump-obama-jfk-7662563/|title=Pop Star Performances at Presidential Inaugurations: A Modern Timeline From JFK to Obama to Trump|last=Payne|first=Chris|magazine=Billboard|access-date=May 7, 2021|date=January 20, 2017}}</ref> Martin's view of Bush changed over the [[Iraq War]], as expressed in his declaration to [[BBC News]] that he will "always condemn war and those who promulgate it". He also stuck up his [[The finger|middle finger]] while singing the president's name in his 2003 song "[[Asignatura Pendiente]]" at a concert.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6369705.stm|title=Ricky Martin defends Bush gesture|publisher=[[BBC News]]|access-date=May 7, 2021|date=February 16, 2007|archive-date=October 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028090722/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6369705.stm|url-status=live}}</ref> At the 2010 ''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards, Martin expressed his disagreement with the [[Arizona SB 1070]] bill, a proposed law that would have required police officers to request documents from individuals whom they suspected to be illegal immigrants.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/ricky-martin-criticizes-arizonas-immigration-law-1207580/|title=Ricky Martin Criticizes Arizona's Immigration Law|magazine=Billboard|date=April 30, 2010|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206073152/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-keys-reconstructed-houses-puerto-rico-8487747/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref> Martin campaigned for the 44th [[president of the United States]] [[Barack Obama]] in 2008 and 2012, and thanked him for an "outstanding presidency" in 2016, while calling him "an amazing leader". Also in 2016, he was an active ally to the [[List of United States Democratic Party presidential candidates|Democratic Party presidential candidate]] [[Hillary Clinton]] campaign, while condemning [[Donald Trump]]'s hateful comments about immigrants.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-president-obama-thanks-instagram-7572341/|title=Ricky Martin Thanks President Obama for an 'Outstanding' Presidency|last=Flores|first=Griselda|magazine=Billboard|date=November 8, 2016|access-date=February 6, 2022|archive-date=February 6, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206150258/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-president-obama-thanks-instagram-7572341/|url-status=live}}</ref> He also performed his hits during the "Hillary Clinton: She's With Us" concert at [[Greek Theatre (Los Angeles)|the Greek Theatre]] on June 6, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/hillary-clinton-ricky-martin-christina-aguilera-shes-with-us-concert-7400186/|title=Ricky Martin, Christina Aguilera, John Legend & Stevie Wonder Play Hillary Clinton's 'She's With Us' Concert|last=Flores|first=Griselda|magazine=Billboard|access-date=May 8, 2021|date=June 7, 2016|archive-date=May 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206150220/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/hillary-clinton-ricky-martin-christina-aguilera-shes-with-us-concert-7400186/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Telegramgate, also known as Chatgate,<ref>{{cite magazine|title='Chatgate' Scandal Plunges Puerto Rico Governor into Political Crisis|url=https://time.com/5627187/puerto-rico-ricardo-rossello-chatgate/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716040854/https://time.com/5627187/puerto-rico-ricardo-rossello-chatgate/|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 16, 2019|magazine=Time|date=July 16, 2019|access-date=July 23, 2019|first1=Michael|last1=Weissenstein|first2=Joel|last2=Colon}}</ref> was a political scandal involving [[Ricardo Rosselló]], then [[Governor of Puerto Rico]], which began on July 8, 2019, with the leak of hundreds of pages of a group chat on the messaging application [[Telegram (software)|Telegram]] between Rosselló and members of his cabinet. The messages were considered vulgar, misogynistic, and homophobic toward several individuals and groups, including Martin. Therefore, Martin, Bad Bunny, Residente and several other artists, and more than half a million Puerto Ricans led the call to take to the streets of Puerto Rico, demanding Rosselló's resignation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/marchadelpueblopuertoricoclamalarenunciadelgobernadorricardorossello-2507138/|title=Marcha del pueblo: Puerto Rico clama la renuncia del gobernador Ricardo Rosselló|date=July 22, 2019|work=El Nuevo Dia|access-date=March 11, 2021|archive-date=October 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015070647/https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/marchadelpueblopuertoricoclamalarenunciadelgobernadorricardorossello-2507138/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Serrano|first1=Oscar J.|title=WhatsApp Gate 2.0: Nuevo chat expone a la Administración Rosselló|url=https://www.noticel.com/ahora/gobierno/whatsapp-gate-20-nuevo-chat-expone-a-la-administracion-rossello/1093250289|website=[[NotiCel]]|access-date=July 19, 2019|language=es|date=July 13, 2019|archive-date=July 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727235312/https://www.noticel.com/ahora/gobierno/whatsapp-gate-20-nuevo-chat-expone-a-la-administracion-rossello/1093250289|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine| url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/puerto-rican-artists-ricky-martin-residente-bad-bunny-governor-resignation-protests-8523379/| title=Puerto Rican Artists Ricky Martin, Residente & Bad Bunny Are Agents of Change Calling for Governor's Resignation| magazine=Billboard| access-date=March 11, 2021| date=July 22, 2019}}</ref> In September 2020, Martin, Luis Fonsi, and actress [[Eva Longoria]] attended a campaign event in [[Kissimmee, Florida]] to support the Democratic presidential candidate [[Joe Biden]] for the [[2020 United States presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-panned-for-playing-despacito-off-his-phone-at-hispanic-heritage-month-event|title=Biden panned for playing 'Despacito' at Hispanic Heritage Month event|last=Wulfsohn|first=Joseph A.|publisher=Fox News|date=September 8, 2020|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193826/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/biden-panned-for-playing-despacito-off-his-phone-at-hispanic-heritage-month-event|url-status=live}}</ref> During an interview with ''Variety'', Martin stated: "I've been supporting Biden forever, I think he is the only option we have and he is great and he has been in politics all his life. This is the moment. We all need to get together and be loud about the course of this nation."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/video/ricky-martin-joe-biden-latino-donald-trump/|title=Ricky Martin Calls Latino Support of Trump 'Super Sad'|last=Malkin|first=Marc|work=Variety|date=October 26, 2020|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193834/https://variety.com/video/ricky-martin-joe-biden-latino-donald-trump/|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the election of Biden as 46th president of the United States, Martin said "Bye-bye" to Trump on social media,<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/joe-biden-wins-president-2020-election-9479373/|title=Joe Biden Defeats Donald Trump in 2020 Presidential Election: Artists React|magazine=Billboard|date=November 7, 2020|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193840/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/joe-biden-wins-president-2020-election-9479373/|url-status=live}}</ref> and shared a photo of himself along with Biden on Instagram.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CHTfFpyHijY/|title=Mr. President-elect @joebiden, thank you for your integrity and unifying spirit. As a Puerto Rican, I am honored to have worked with you and your team on this difficult campaign. I was able to feel your passion firsthand, inspiring and contagious.|last=Martin|first=Ricky|via=Instagram|access-date=February 7, 2022|date=January 21, 2022|url-status=live|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/ricky_martin/2437428551241050328}}</ref>

In May 2021, Martin demonstrated his support for the [[Ni una menos]] movement, condemning femicides and [[violence against women]] in Puerto Rico, while calling authorities to protect women. He further expressed that no woman should fear for her safety and urged authorities to take steps in order to prevent these acts.<ref>{{cite news|title=El mensaje de Ricky Martin en su lucha contra la violencia de género|trans-title=Ricky Martin's message in his fight against gender violence|url=https://www.a24.com/show/el-mensaje-ricky-martin-su-lucha-contra-la-violencia-genero-n830460|work=[[América 24|A24]]|date=May 8, 2021|language=Spanish|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=May 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508134716/https://www.a24.com/show/el-mensaje-ricky-martin-su-lucha-contra-la-violencia-genero-n830460|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same month, he supported the [[2021 Colombian protests]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://okdiario.com/look/actualidad/mensajes-apoyo-celebrities-colombia-1180293/fotos|title=De Shakira a Kendall Jenner: las redes se inundan con mensajes de apoyo a Colombia|work=[[Okdiario]]|language=es|date=May 5, 2021|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193902/https://okdiario.com/look/actualidad/mensajes-apoyo-celebrities-colombia-1180293/fotos|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, the singer raised his voice in support of the [[2021 Cuban protests]] against the [[Raúl Castro|Castro]] regime for the restrictions due to the COVID-19 pandemic and the economic crisis, stating: "This is very important. Our brothers and sisters in Cuba need us to inform the world what they are experiencing today. Let's fill the networks before they remove the internet in the country. Humanitarian aid for Cuba NOW."<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ricky Martin, Rosalía y otros artistas apoyaron las protestas contra el régimen en Cuba|url=https://www.ambito.com/mundo/cuba/ricky-martin-rosalia-y-otros-artistas-apoyaron-las-protestas-contra-el-regimen-n5220153|work=[[Ámbito Financiero]]|language=es|date=July 12, 2021|access-date=February 7, 2022|archive-date=February 7, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193910/https://www.ambito.com/mundo/cuba/ricky-martin-rosalia-y-otros-artistas-apoyaron-las-protestas-contra-el-regimen-n5220153|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== LGBT advocacy ===
[[File:Ricky Martin 2010.jpg|thumb|left|Martin giving a speech at the 14th Annual [[Human Rights Campaign]].]]
As a gay man, Martin actively supports [[LGBT rights by country or territory|LGBT rights worldwide]] since his coming out in 2010.<ref name="Latin Post LGBT">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latinpost.com/articles/3576/20131106/ricky-martin-russian-anti-gay-laws-russia-discrimination-russian-laws-perez-hilton-russian-t-shirt-campaign.htm|title=Ricky Martin Who Once Bullied Gays, Now Fights Against Russian Anti-Gay Laws|last=Castellanos|first=Melissa|publisher=Latin Post|date=November 6, 2013|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214041/https://www.latinpost.com/articles/3576/20131106/ricky-martin-russian-anti-gay-laws-russia-discrimination-russian-laws-perez-hilton-russian-t-shirt-campaign.htm|url-status=live}}</ref> Even before coming out, he was noted by the mainstream media for being popular among gay men and having a large gay fan base. He also went on the cover of the American [[LGBT]]-interest magazine ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]'' in July 1999.<ref>{{cite journal|year=1999|last=Griffiths|first=John|title=Cover Story: Ricky Martin cross appeal|journal=The Advocate|page=26|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA26|access-date=February 7, 2022|issn=0001-8996|volume=74|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193918/https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA26|archive-date=February 7, 2022|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|year=1999|last=Griffiths|first=John|title=Cover Story: Ricky Martin cross appeal|journal=The Advocate|page=28|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA28|access-date=February 7, 2022|issn=0001-8996|volume=74|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193925/https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA28|archive-date=February 7, 2022|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|year=1999|last=Griffiths|first=John|title=Cover Story: Ricky Martin cross appeal|journal=The Advocate|page=31|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA31|access-date=February 7, 2022|issn=0001-8996|volume=74|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207193931/https://books.google.com/books?id=qWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA31|archive-date=February 7, 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite this, he admitted that he felt homosexuality was evil since he was raised as a Catholic and targeted his anger toward others, especially gay men: "I was very angry, very rebellious. I used to look at gay men and think, 'I'm not like that, I don't want to be like that, that's not me.' I was ashamed." He added that he "had internalized [[homophobia]]" back then.<ref name="Latin Post LGBT"/><ref name="PinkNews LGBT">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2013/08/27/ricky-martin-i-used-to-bully-people-i-knew-were-gay/|title=Ricky Martin: 'I used to bully people I knew were gay'|last=Carter|first=Daniel|work=PinkNews|date=August 27, 2013|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214122/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2013/08/27/ricky-martin-i-used-to-bully-people-i-knew-were-gay/|url-status=live}}</ref> He is currently considered to be a [[gay icon]],<ref>Citations regarding Martin as a gay icon:
* {{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3111819/bad-bunny-caro-video-lgbtq-inclusive/|title=How Bad Bunny Bridges LGBTQ And Latinx Identities With His Inclusive 'Caro' Video|last=Villa|first=Lucas|publisher=MTV News|date=February 6, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214147/http://www.mtv.com/news/3111819/bad-bunny-caro-video-lgbtq-inclusive/|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/news/ricky-martin-las-vegas-residency-special-air|title=Ricky Martin: Las Vegas Residency Special To Air|last=Merrill|first=Philip|publisher=Grammy Awards|date=August 23, 2017|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214148/https://www.grammy.com/news/ricky-martin-las-vegas-residency-special-air|url-status=live}}
* {{cite news|url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/maluma-and-ricky-martin-team-up-for-sizzling-no-se-me-quita-music-video/|title=Maluma and Ricky Martin team up for sizzling No Se Me Quita music video|last=Megarry|first=Daniel|work=Gay Times|access-date=August 8, 2021|date=August 30, 2019|archive-date=August 8, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210808111640/https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/maluma-and-ricky-martin-team-up-for-sizzling-no-se-me-quita-music-video/|url-status=live}}
* {{cite news|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/04/23/who-has-ricky-martin-dated-open-relationships-madonna-gay-marriage/|title=Who has Ricky Martin dated? From a rumoured fling with Madonna to being a gay father of two|work=PinkNews|last=Finamore|first=Emma|date=April 23, 2010|access-date=January 21, 2022|archive-date=January 21, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121191557/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/04/23/who-has-ricky-martin-dated-open-relationships-madonna-gay-marriage/|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://www.out.com/music/2019/8/30/ricky-martin-maluma-cant-get-taste-out-their-mouths|title=Watch Ricky Martin and Maluma in Baywatch-Inspired Music Video|last=Anderson|first=Tre'vell|work=Out|date=August 30, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214238/https://www.out.com/music/2019/8/30/ricky-martin-maluma-cant-get-taste-out-their-mouths|url-status=live}}
* {{Cite web|url=https://instinctmagazine.com/maluma-and-ricky-martin-teamed-up-for-a-new-mv/|title=Maluma And Ricky Martin Teamed Up For A New MV|last=Randall|first=Devin|work=Instinct|date=August 31, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214242/https://instinctmagazine.com/maluma-and-ricky-martin-teamed-up-for-a-new-mv/|url-status=live}}</ref> with ''[[PinkNews]]'' labeling him "a strong advocate of LGBT rights" who "expressed support for equal marriage" since coming out.<ref name="PinkNews LGBT"/>

As the first mainstream Latin music artist to come out,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vervetimes.com/ricky-martin-i-wasnt-misleading-anyone-when-i-dated-women/|title=Ricky Martin: I Wasn't Misleading Anyone When I Dated Women|last=Fedirighi|first=Craig|work=Verve Times|date=June 3, 2021|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214336/https://vervetimes.com/ricky-martin-i-wasnt-misleading-anyone-when-i-dated-women/|url-status=live}}</ref> Martin's coming out was a game-changer for "Latin Pride". ''Billboard''{{'}}s Lucas Villa stated: "With Martin's announcement, gay artists, who had long kept their sexual identities a secret, finally had a beacon of hope. If Martin could come out with his career unscathed, there was hope for other artists in Latin music to start doing the same." He added that since then, "a growing number of Latin artists have either come out after years in the spotlight, or many have simply started their careers by embracing their gay identities".<ref name="Billboard Pride"/> In 2010, [[GLAAD]] then-president [[Jarrett Barrios]] expressed that Martin's coming out as gay leads "hundreds of millions of people" to have "a cultural connection with an artist, a celebrity and, perhaps most importantly, a father who happens to be gay", adding that "his decision to model this kind of openness and honesty can lead to greater acceptance for countless gay people in U.S., in Latin America and worldwide".<ref name="People Reveal"/> In 2019, [[Human Rights Campaign]] then-president [[Alphonso David]] expressed that Martin "has used his international stage to advocate for LGBTQ people around the world" with his "unique voice and passionate activism".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metroweekly.com/2019/09/ricky-martin-dominique-jackson-to-be-honored-at-human-rights-campaigns-national-dinner|title=Ricky Martin, Dominique Jackson to be honored at Human Rights Campaign's National Dinner|last=Riley|first=John|work=Metro Weekly|date=September 25, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214354/https://www.metroweekly.com/2019/09/ricky-martin-dominique-jackson-to-be-honored-at-human-rights-campaigns-national-dinner|url-status=live}}</ref> The following year, [[Suzy Exposito]] from ''Rolling Stone'' argued that with risking his career and coming out, Martin "set the scene for Bad Bunny to be free in many ways that, during his own breakthrough moment, he could not".<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/bad-bunny-cover-story-lockdown-puerto-rico-new-albums-996871/|title=Bad Bunny in Captivity|last=Exposito|first=Suzy|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=May 14, 2020|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208114134/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/bad-bunny-cover-story-lockdown-puerto-rico-new-albums-996871/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Martin expressed support for [[same-sex marriage]] during an interview on ''[[Larry King Live]]'' in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.samesame.com.au/news/international/6110/Let_Ricky_Martin_get_married|title=Let Ricky Martin get married!|last=Akersten|first=Matt|publisher=SameSame|date=November 11, 2010|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=November 13, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101113135622/http://www.samesame.com.au/news/international/6110/Let_Ricky_Martin_get_married|url-status=dead}}</ref> He has then delivered speeches about LGBT rights at the [[LGBT rights at the United Nations|United Nations Homophobia Conference]], the [[GLAAD Media Award]]s, and the Human Rights Campaign. He also raised his voice to support gay marriage in Puerto Rico before its legalization in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://watchmojo.com/video/id/19787|title=Top 10 Inspirational LGBTQ+ Celebrities|publisher=WatchMojo|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214437/https://watchmojo.com/video/id/19787|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hrc.org/news/hrc-ricky-martin-to-speak-at-vigil-remembering-lgbtq-lives-lost-in-puerto-r|title=Human Rights Campaign, Ricky Martin to Speak at Vigil Remembering LGBTQ Lives Lost in Puerto Rico|last=Morales|first=Alberto|publisher=[[Human Rights Campaign]]|date=May 15, 2020|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214448/https://www.hrc.org/news/hrc-ricky-martin-to-speak-at-vigil-remembering-lgbtq-lives-lost-in-puerto-r|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2016, Martin met with Chilean LGBT rights group Fundación Iguales to learn about the challenges LGBT citizens face there. AT the meeting, he said that he wants "equal marriage rights for Chile" and he wants his sons to grow up in a world where "there are no second-class citizens".<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.latinpost.com/articles/117759/20160307/ricky-martin-unites-with-chilean-activists-for-lgbt-rights-in-the-latin-american-country.htm| title=Ricky Martin Calls for Marriage Equality in Chile| access-date=July 18, 2020 |date=March 7, 2016|last=Contreras|first=Milly|publisher=Latin Post|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214505/https://www.latinpost.com/articles/117759/20160307/ricky-martin-unites-with-chilean-activists-for-lgbt-rights-in-the-latin-american-country.htm|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.efe.com/efe/english/entertainment/ricky-martin-stands-up-for-same-sex-marriage-in-chile/50000264-2859522| title=Ricky Martin stands up for same-sex marriage in Chile| access-date=July 18, 2020 |date=March 6, 2016|publisher=EFE|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214516/https://www.efe.com/efe/english/entertainment/ricky-martin-stands-up-for-same-sex-marriage-in-chile/50000264-2859522|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the Colombia's highest court voting against an anti same-sex marriage proposal in April 2016, Martin tweeted: "Love and equality win, Colombia says YES to same-sex marriage."<ref>{{cite magazine| url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-juanes-react-colombia-same-sex-marriage-7326432/| title=Ricky Martin, Juanes & More React to Colombia's Ruling in Favor of Same-Sex Marriage| access-date=October 19, 2020 |date=April 8, 2016|last=Flores|first=Griselda|magazine=Billboard|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214534/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/ricky-martin-juanes-react-colombia-same-sex-marriage-7326432/|url-status=live}}</ref> During an interview with ''[[New York (magazine)#Vulture|Vulture]]'', Martin talked about his role in ''The Assassination of Gianni Versace'' and how he wanted his portrayal to help "normalize open relationships".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/02/ricky-martin-on-american-crime-story-versace-and-coming-out.html|title=Ricky Martin on ACS: Versace, Coming Out, and 'Normalizing' Open Relationships|last=Jung|first=E. Alex|work=[[New York (magazine)#Vulture|Vulture]]|date=February 14, 2018|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214545/https://www.vulture.com/2018/02/ricky-martin-on-american-crime-story-versace-and-coming-out.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2019, he published an open letter slamming the [[Religious freedom bill|religious liberty bill]], saying: "As a defender of human rights and a member of the LGBTT community, I am vehemently opposed to the proposed measure imposed upon us under the guise of religious freedom, that projects us to the world as a backwards country." Puerto Rico's then-governor backed down and withdrew his support of the bill following Martin's statement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/ricky-martin-slams-religious-liberty-bill-puerto-rico-governor-backs-n1017246|title=Ricky Martin slams 'religious liberty' bill. Puerto Rico's governor backs down.|last=Acevedo|first=Nicole|publisher=NBC News|date=June 13, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208214555/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/ricky-martin-slams-religious-liberty-bill-puerto-rico-governor-backs-n1017246|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2020, Martin performed his song "[[Recuerdo (song)|Recuerdo]]" with Carla Morrison for a virtual event, Can't Cancel Pride: Helping LGBTQ+ People in Need, to raise visibility and funds for LGBTQ+ communities.<ref>{{cite magazine| url=https://ew.com/events/katy-perry-ricky-martin-joining-pg-iheartradio-virtual-pride-event| title=Katy Perry, Ricky Martin, and more stars join P&G and iHeartRadio's virtual Pride event|last=Yang|first=Rachel|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=July 18, 2020 |date=June 17, 2020|archive-date=August 15, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815170210/https://ew.com/events/katy-perry-ricky-martin-joining-pg-iheartradio-virtual-pride-event/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/celebrities/2020/06/25/katy-perry-ricky-martin-celebrate-lgbtq-cant-cancel-pride/3261838001| title=Katy Perry, Ricky Martin, more celebrate LGBTQ+ community with 'Can't Cancel Pride' event|last=Henderson|first=Cydney|work=USA Today|access-date=July 18, 2020 |date=June 25, 2020|archive-date=August 15, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815170204/https://www.usatoday.com/story/entertainment/celebrities/2020/06/25/katy-perry-ricky-martin-celebrate-lgbtq-cant-cancel-pride/3261838001/|url-status=live}}</ref> He appeared at the virtual event in the following year as well.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2021/digital/news/demi-lovato-lil-nas-x-cant-cancel-pride-concert-1234977237/|title=Demi Lovato, Lil Nas X, Ricky Martin to Appear at Virtual 'Can't Cancel Pride' Benefit Concert|last=Aswad|first=Jem|work=Variety|date=May 20, 2021|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215731/https://variety.com/2021/digital/news/demi-lovato-lil-nas-x-cant-cancel-pride-concert-1234977237/|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2021, Martin was named national [[spokesperson]] for the [[Pulse Memorial and Museum|onePULSE Foundation]], a non-profit organization that focuses on managing "the design and construction of the permanent national memorial and museum dedicated to the [[Orlando nightclub shooting|Pulse nightclub tragedy]]".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/746120/ricky-martin-named-national-spokesperson-for-onepulse-foundation/|title=Ricky Martin Named National Spokesperson For onePULSE Foundation|last=Darmon|first=Aynslee|work=Entertainment Tonight Canada|date=February 11, 2021|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215755/https://etcanada.com/news/746120/ricky-martin-named-national-spokesperson-for-onepulse-foundation/|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, he expressed that he wants to "normalize families like" his, in an interview with ''People''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/ricky-martin-normalize-families-like-his-pride/|title=Father of Four Ricky Martin Says He Wants to 'Normalize Families Like Mine': 'I'm Very Happy'|last=VanHoose|first=Benjamin|work=People|date=June 7, 2021|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215803/https://people.com/parents/ricky-martin-normalize-families-like-his-pride/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Several of Martin's music videos feature diversity in sexual orientations and same-sex couples, including "[[The Best Thing About Me Is You]]",<ref name="GLAAD Ruso">{{Cite web|url=https://www.glaad.org/2011/03/21/video-ricky-martin-accepts-the-vito-russo-award-at-the-glaad-media-awards-in-new-york?page=10&response_type=embed|title=Video: Ricky Martin Accepts the Vito Russo Award at the GLAAD Media Awards in New York|publisher=[[GLAAD]]|date=March 21, 2011|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215817/https://www.glaad.org/2011/03/21/video-ricky-martin-accepts-the-vito-russo-award-at-the-glaad-media-awards-in-new-york?page=10&response_type=embed|url-status=live}}</ref> "[[Disparo al Corazón]]",<ref name="Billboard Pride"/> "[[Fiebre (Ricky Martin song)|Fiebre]]",<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/03/06/ricky-martin-celebrates-his-sexuality-and-gets-very-raunchy-with-other-men-in-new-fiebre-video/|title=Ricky Martin celebrates his sexuality and gets very raunchy with other men in new Fiebre video|last=Bloodworth|first=Adam|work=PinkNews|access-date=August 2, 2021|date=March 6, 2018|archive-date=August 2, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802123748/https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/03/06/ricky-martin-celebrates-his-sexuality-and-gets-very-raunchy-with-other-men-in-new-fiebre-video/|url-status=live}}</ref> and "[[Tiburones]]".<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.cadena3.com/noticia/espectaculos/el-guino-de-ricky-martin-al-aborto-en-la-cancion-tiburones_251364| title=El guiño de Ricky Martin al aborto en la canción 'Tiburones'| publisher=Cadena 3 Argentina| access-date=February 27, 2021| date=January 24, 2020| language=es| archive-date=March 1, 2021| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301214015/https://www.cadena3.com/noticia/espectaculos/el-guino-de-ricky-martin-al-aborto-en-la-cancion-tiburones_251364| url-status=live}}</ref> For his activism and advocacy for LGBTQ community, Martin has been honored with numerous accolades, including the [[GLAAD Vito Russo Award]],<ref name="GLAAD Ruso"/> the Gala Vanguard Award by the [[Los Angeles LGBT Center]],<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/pride/ricky-martin-honored-los-angeles-lgbt-center-gala-vanguard-awards-8471705/amp/|title=Ricky Martin to Be Honored at Los Angeles LGBT Center's Gala Vanguard Awards|last=Bote|first=Joshua|magazine=Billboard|date=August 22, 2018|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215853/https://www.billboard.com/culture/pride/ricky-martin-honored-los-angeles-lgbt-center-gala-vanguard-awards-8471705/amp/|url-status=live}}</ref> the International Icon Award by the [[British LGBT Awards]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/british-lgbt-award-nominees-revealed-with-ricky-martin-to-receive-accolade-36580315.html|title=British LGBT Award nominees revealed with Ricky Martin to receive accolade|last=Nerssessian|first=Joe|work=The Independent|date=February 7, 2018|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215902/https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/british-lgbt-award-nominees-revealed-with-ricky-martin-to-receive-accolade-36580315.html|url-status=live}}</ref> the National Visibility Award by the Human Rights Campaign,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hrc.org/news/hrc-to-honor-ricky-martin-at-23rd-annual-national-dinner|title=HRC to Honor Ricky Martin at 23rd Annual National Dinner|last=Morrow|first=Nick|publisher=Human Rights Campaign|date=September 18, 2019|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215909/https://www.hrc.org/news/hrc-to-honor-ricky-martin-at-23rd-annual-national-dinner|url-status=live}}</ref> the Trailblazer Award by the LGBT Center Dinner,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/anna-wintour-emma-gonzalez-ricky-martin-lgbt-center-new-york-city-dinner|title=The LGBT Center Dinner Honors Anna Wintour, Emma González, and Ricky Martin|last=Barsamian|first=Edward|work=Vogue|date=April 20, 2018|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215937/https://www.vogue.com/article/anna-wintour-emma-gonzalez-ricky-martin-lgbt-center-new-york-city-dinner|url-status=live}}</ref> the Celebrity Activist of the Year by ''[[LGBTQ Nation]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2020/10/lgbtq-nation-heroes-year/|title=And the LGBTQ Nation Heroes of the Year are...|last=Holmes|first=Juwan J.|work=LGBTQ Nation|date=October 1, 2020|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208215950/https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2020/10/lgbtq-nation-heroes-year/|url-status=live}}</ref> and the Legacy Award by [[Attitude (magazine)|''Attitude'' Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://attitude.co.uk/article/attitude-legend-award-supported-by-virgin-holidays-ricky-martin/19316/|title=Attitude Legend Award with Virgin Holidays|work=Attitude|date=October 11, 2018|access-date=February 8, 2022|archive-date=February 8, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220208220000/https://attitude.co.uk/article/attitude-legend-award-supported-by-virgin-holidays-ricky-martin/19316/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Achievements==
{{See also|List of awards and nominations received by Ricky Martin}}
[[File:Ricky Martin Walk of Fame.jpg|thumb|left|Martin's star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]]]]
Throughout his career, Martin has won over 200 awards (most awarded male Latin artist),<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/pop-culture/what-happened-ricky-martin-before-pictures-go-viral-recent-appearance-sends-internet-meltdown|title=What happened to Ricky Martin? Before and after pictures go viral as recent appearance sends internet into meltdown|publisher=Sportskeeda|last=Roy|first=Barsha|access-date=January 30, 2022|date=October 1, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aarp.org/espanol/entretenimiento/musica-cultura/info-2015/fotos-ricky-martin-carrera-historia.html|title=Ricky Martin cumple 50 años|last=Rodas de Juárez|first=Celeste|publisher=[[AARP]]|language=es|date=December 23, 2021|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://hellomusictheory.com/learn/famous-lgbtq-singers/|title=15 Of The Greatest And Most Famous LGBTQ+ Singers|last=Farrant|first=Dan|publisher=Hello Music Theory|access-date=April 11, 2022}}</ref> including two [[Grammy Awards]],<ref name="Grammy"/> five [[Latin Grammy Awards]],<ref>
* {{cite magazine|title=Sanz, Juanes Top Winners At 2nd Latin Grammys|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/sanz-juanes-top-winners-at-2nd-latin-grammys-77905/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=December 13, 2014|date=October 30, 2001}}
* {{cite news|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/ricky-martin/17058|title=Ricky Martin|publisher=Grammy Awards|access-date=May 19, 2021}}
* {{cite news|title=List of Winners at Thursday's 8th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/92410793/the-desert-sun/|newspaper=The Desert Sun|date=November 10, 2007|page=52|via=Newspapers.com|access-date=January 12, 2022}}
* {{cite news| url=https://www.latingrammy.com/en/nominees| title=Nominees 21st Annual Latin Grammy Awards| publisher=Latin Grammy Awards| access-date=November 20, 2020 |date=November 19, 2020}}</ref> five [[MTV Video Music Awards]] (tied for most wins by a Latin artist),<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2022-mtv-vma-performers-anitta-1235122878/|title=Anitta, Panic! at the Disco, J Balvin & More to Perform at 2022 MTV VMAs|last=Greun|first=Paul|work=Billboare|access-date=August 9, 2022|date=August 5, 2022}}</ref> two [[American Music Awards]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theamas.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=%22Ricky+Martin%22&winnerYear=|title=Winners Database|publisher=[[American Music Awards]]|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> three [[Latin American Music Awards]],<ref name="Latin AMAs"/> three [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/music-news/miley-cyrus-ricky-martin-set-701634/|title=Miley Cyrus, Ricky Martin Set to Perform on 2014 Billboard Music Awards|last=Trakin|first=Roy|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 6, 2014|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> a ''Billboard'' Music Video Award,<ref name="Billboard MV Award"/> nine [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]],<ref>
* {{cite magazine|last1=Lannert|first1=John|title=10th Annual Latin Music Conference|magazine=Billboard|date=April 24, 1999|volume=111|issue=17|pages=LM-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eigEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA49|access-date=March 6, 2016}}
* {{cite magazine|year=2000|title=Awardee List|magazine=Billboard|page=16|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EA8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=RA1-PA16|access-date=May 19, 2021|issn=0006-2510|volume=106}}
* {{cite magazine|title=Juan Gabriel Cleans Up At Billboard Latin Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/juan-gabriel-cleans-up-at-billboard-latin-awards-75804/|magazine=Billboard|access-date=February 6, 2022|date=May 10, 2002}}
* {{cite news|title=Ricky Martin honored at Latin Billboard awards|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/94569089/victoria-advocate/|newspaper=[[The Victoria Advocate]]|date=September 24, 1999|page=63|via=Newspapers.com|access-date=February 9, 2022}}
* {{cite magazine|year=2004|title=Latin Awards|magazine=Billboard|page=67|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xRAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA67|access-date=November 15, 2021|issn=0006-2510|volume=72}}
* {{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/2006-billboard-latin-music-awards-winners-58598/|title=2006 Billboard Latin Music Awards Winners|magazine=Billboard|date=April 28, 2006|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> eight [[World Music Awards]],<ref>
* {{cite magazine|year=1999|title=1999 World Music Awards|magazine=Billboard|page=61|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tQ0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA61|access-date=February 9, 2022|issn=0006-2510|volume=140}}
* {{cite magazine|year=2000|title=2000 World Music Awards|magazine=Billboard|page=53|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mg8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA53|access-date=February 9, 2022|issn=0006-2510|volume=98}}
* {{cite magazine|year=2001|title=2001 World Music Awards|magazine=Billboard|page=65|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DRQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA65|access-date=February 9, 2022|issn=0006-2510|volume=130}}
* {{Cite web|url=http://www.worldmusicawards.com/index.php/news/global-superstars-will-rock-monte-carlo-world-music-awards-air-wednesday-may-28-nbc/|title=Global Superstars Will Rock Monte Carlo At The World Music Awards, To Air Wednesday, May 28 On Nbc|publisher=[[World Music Awards]]|date=April 28, 2006|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> fourteen [[Lo Nuestro Awards]] (including the [[Lo Nuestro Excellence Award|Excellence Award]]),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.univision.com/shows/premio-lo-nuestro/foto-a-foto-asi-se-vivio-la-espectacular-primera-gala-de-la-decada-de-premio-lo-nuestro-fotos|title=Foto a foto, así se vivió la espectacular primera gala de la década de Premio Lo Nuestro|publisher=Univision|language=es|date=February 21, 2020|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> and a ''[[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]]''.<ref name="Guinness"/> As an actor, he was nominated for an [[Emmy Awards|Emmy Award]].<ref name="Emmy"/> In 2007, Martin was honored with a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]], located at 6901 Hollywood Blvd.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/entertainment/celebrities/2020/06/16/ricky-martins-life-and-career-photographs/3200837001/|title=Ricky Martin: The international pop sensation's life through the years|work=USA Today|date=June 17, 2020|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://walkoffame.com/ricky-martin/|title=Ricky Martin|date=October 25, 2019|publisher=[[Hollywood Walk of Fame]]|access-date=February 10, 2022}}</ref>

Martin is ranked among the Greatest Latin Artists of All Time and the Greatest Hot Latin Songs Artists of All Time by ''Billboard'',<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-of-all-time-latin-artists/|title=Greatest of All Time Latin Artists|magazine=Billboard|date=October 19, 2020|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/greatest-hot-latin-songs-artists/|title=Greatest Of All Time Hot Latin Songs Artists|magazine=Billboard|date=October 17, 2016|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> while his album ''Vuelve'' was placed at number five on ''Billboard''{{'}}s Top 20 Latin Albums Of All Time in 2018.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Roiz|first=Jessica |title=The Top 20 Latin Albums of All Time |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/top-20-latin-albums-of-all-time/ |magazine=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |access-date=May 8, 2020 |date=September 20, 2018}}</ref> In 1998, his song, "Perdido Sin Ti" reached the top of the Latin Pop Airplay chart, displacing Martin's own "Vuelve", making him the first artist on the chart's history to replace himself.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Chart Beat: U2, Rick Ross and Miley Cyrus |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/chart-beat-u2-rick-ross-miley-cyrus/ |access-date=June 4, 2009|date=March 12, 2009 |magazine=Billboard |first=Fred |last=Bronson |publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc  }}</ref> His song "Livin' la Vida Loca" became the first number-one song on ''Billboard'' Hot 100, which was made entirely in Pro Tools,<ref name="Billboard Harley">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/ricky-martin-livin-la-vida-loca-pro-tools-desmond-child/|title='We've Crossed the Threshold': How Ricky Martin's 'Livin' La Vida Loca' Became the First No. 1 Song Made Entirely in Pro Tools|last=Brown|first=Harley|magazine=Billboard|access-date=May 17, 2021|date=May 10, 2019}}</ref> and achieved the first number one hit for his label, Columbia.<ref>{{cite magazine|year=1999|title=C2 Says: Oh, Ricky, You're So Fine|magazine=Billboard|page=86|publisher=Nielsen Business Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eQ0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA86|access-date=May 22, 2021|issn=0006-2510|volume=88}}</ref> It also became the first song in history to top ''Billboard''{{'}}s [[Adult Top 40|Adult Pop Airplay]], [[Mainstream Top 40|Pop Airplay]], and [[Rhythmic (chart)|Rhythmic Airplay]] charts, holding its record as the only song to do so for 14 years.<ref name="Billboard 24k"/> On May 15, 1999, it became the first single ever to rule four different Billboard charts and made Martin the first act to simultaneously scale a pop, Latin, and dance chart. Two weeks later, he became the first artist to simultaneously top the ''Billboard'' 200, Hot Latin Tracks, [[Dance Club Songs|Hot Dance Music/Club Play]], [[Dance/Electronic Singles Sales|Hot Dance Music/Maxi-Singles Sales]], [[Top 40 Tracks]], and the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name="Interscope"/> His song "Tal Vez" (2003) marked the first number one debut on ''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Juanes' 'Me Enamora,' Mana's 'Labios Compartidos' & More No. 1 Debuts on Hot Latin Songs |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/juanes-me-enamora-manas-labios-compartidos-more-no-1-debuts-on-hot-7572567/ |magazine=Billboard |access-date=May 4, 2021 |date=November 8, 2016}}</ref> Martin is the first and only artist with [[List of Latin songs on the Billboard Hot 100|Spanish-language entries on ''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in three decades.<ref name="Hot 100"/> In 2020, he became the first and only artist in history to enter the ''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs chart across five decades, including his work as part of Menudo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://preview.houstonchronicle.com/music/ricky-martin-debuts-tiburones-remix-15255167|title=Ricky Martin debuts 'Tiburones (Remix)' quarantine video|last=Guerra|first=Joey|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=May 8, 2020|access-date=May 8, 2020}}</ref> The following year, he became the first male Latin artist in history to have 4 songs from different decades to have over 100 million streams on [[Spotify]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=sitepopmais|author=Portal Pop Mais|number=1475914068305354752|date=December 28, 2021|title=Ricky Martin se junta à Shakira como os únicos artistas latinos com pelo menos uma música em quatro décadas (anos 90, 00s, 10s, 20s) atingindo 100 milhões de streams no Spotify!}}</ref> He owns the record as the artist with most top 20s on the US Latin Pop Airplay chart, with 51 songs,<ref name="Latin Pop Airplay"/><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/ricky-martin-latin-pop-songs-chart-record/|title=Ricky Martin Extends Latin Pop Songs Chart Record|magazine=Billboard|first=Amaya|last=Mendizabal|date=May 29, 2015|access-date=July 25, 2015}}</ref> and is the runner-up of most top 10s.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/muevelo-tops-latin-airplay/| title=Nicky Jam & Daddy Yankee Unite Atop Latin Airplay Chart With 'Muévelo| access-date=April 21, 2020| date=April 2, 2020}}</ref> He is the fourth artist with the most number one songs in the history of the Hot Latin Songs chart.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/vote-favorite-latin-chart-topper-enrique-iglesias-gloria-estefan-7526308/|title=Vote For Your Favorite Latin Chart-Topper: Enrique Iglesias, Luis Miguel, Gloria Estefan and More|magazine=Billboard|date=October 4, 2016|access-date=February 9, 2022}}</ref> Additionally, he holds the record as the most Spanish-language entries on ARIA top 50 singles chart, with three.<ref name="ARIA Come"/>

On October 11, 2007, then-[[mayor of Miami Beach, Florida]] [[David Dermer]] awarded him the [[Freedom of the City|key to the city]] of Miami Beach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://peopleenespanol.com/article/ricky-martin-gets-his-hollywood-star/|title=Ricky Martin Gets His Hollywood Star|work=People en Español|date=October 16, 2007|access-date=February 10, 2022}}</ref> Puerto Rico named August 31 the "International Ricky Martin Day" in 2008.<ref name="MW Nightclub"/> The [[Government of Spain]] granted [[Spanish nationality law|Spanish nationality]] to Martin in 2011, for being "recognized in different artistic facets".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lne.es/sociedad/2011/11/04/ricky-martin-benicio-toro-nacionalidad-21006301.html|title=Ricky Martin y Benicio del Toro ya tienen la nacionalidad española|work=[[La Nueva España]]|language=es|date=November 4, 2011|access-date=February 10, 2022}}</ref> In 2018, in recognition of "his dedication to the island and people of Puerto Rico, his philanthropic work to eliminate human trafficking across the Caribbean, and his commitment to the arts", the singer received a [[proclamation]] naming June 7 the "Ricky Martin Day" in New York City.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www1.nyc.gov/site/mospce/heritage-celebrations/puerto-rican-heritage-reception-2018.page| title=Puerto Rican Heritage Reception 2018| access-date=June 7, 2020 |date=June 7, 2018|publisher=[[Government of New York City]]}}</ref> Throughout his career, Martin has sold over 70 million records making him one of the best-selling Latin music artists of all time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/ricky-martins-life-travel-23-sizzling-pics/|title=Ricky Martin's sun-kissed life in travel, in 19 intimate pics|work=Gay Star News|date=September 15, 2017|access-date=February 10, 2022}}</ref> In 2022, ''[[La Nación]]'' estimated his net worth at US$130 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/estados-unidos/cuanto-cuesta-una-obra-de-jwan-yosef-el-marido-de-ricky-martin-nid01082022/|title=¿Cuánto cuesta una obra de Jwan Yosef, el marido de Ricky Martin?|work=La Nación|language=es|date=August 1, 2022|access-date=August 9, 2022}}</ref>

